Number 1:  Important for exam - AWS Fundamentals:

- There are many more edge locatins than regions
- For this exams , know the AWS Service Types below:
  Containers
  Analytics
  Management and Governance
  Migration and Transfer
  Compute
  Application Integration
  Security, Identity, and Compliance
  Network and Content Delivery
  Storage
  Containers
  AWS Cost Management
  Databases
  AWS Global Infrastructure
 
 - AWS Building Blocks Exam Tips
    - A region is a physical location in the world that consists of two or more AZ
    An AZ is one or more discrete data centers - each with redundant power, network and connectivity - housed in separate facilities
    - Edge locations are endpoints for AWS that are used for caching content.  Typically consists of Cloudfront, Amazon CDN.
    
  
Number 2:  Who owns the Cloud Exam tips
- Shared Responsibility Model
- Can you do this yourself in the console?
  - Security groups, IAM users, patching EC2 OS, patching database, running on EC2, etc
- If not, AWS is likely responsible
  - Management of data centers, security camera, cabling, patching RDS, operating systems, etc
- Encryption is a shared responsibility - both you and AWS


Number 3 - Compute Storage, Databases, and Networking Exam Tips
- Key services to know for the exam:
  - Computer - EC2, Lambda, Elastic Beanstalk
  - Storage - S3, EBS, FSx, Storage Gateway
  - Databases - RDS, DynamoDB, Redshift
  - Networking - VPC's, Direct Connect, Route 53, API Gateway, Global Accelerator
 
 Number 4 - AWS Well Architected Framework Pillars Exam Tips
   - Most Important for the exam:
      - Read the whitepaper after finishing the course:  Well Architected Framework Whitepaper
    
    - 5 pillars of the Well-Architected Framework
      - Operational Excellence - focuses on running and monitoring systems to deliver business value, and continually improving processes and proceedures
    - Performance Efficience - Focuses on using IT and computing resources efficienctly
    - Security - Focuses on protecting information and systems
    - Cost Optimization - Focuses on avoiding unnessarary costs
    - Reliability - Focuses on ensuring workload performs its inteded function corretly and consistent when its expected to 
    
 Number 5 - AWS Fundamentals Exam Tips (Entire Section Covered)
   - 3 Tips for AWS Building Blocks
      - A Region - is a physical location in the world that consistes of two or more AZ's 
      - An AZ is one or more discrete data centers - each with redundant power, networking, and connectivity - housed in separate facilities
      - Edge locations are the endpoints for AWS that are used for caching content.  Typically, this consists of Cloudfront, Amazon's content delivery network (CDN)
   
   - Can you do this yourself in the AWS management console?
      - If yes you are likely responsible
        - Security groups, IAM users, patching EC2 OS, patching databases running on EC2, etc
      - If not, AWS is likely responsible
        - Managemetn of data centers, security cameras, cabling, patching, RDS, OS, etc
     
     - Encryption is a shared responsibility
     
     - Key Services to know for the exam
        - Compute - EC2, Lambda, Elastic Beanstalk
        - Storage - S3, EBS, eFS, FSx, Storage Gateway
        - Databases - RDS, DynamoDB, Redshift
        - Networking - VPCs, Direct Connect, Route 53, API Gateway, AWS global Accererator
        
      - Before the exam, read the whitepaper - Well Architected Framework Whitepaper
